     <p align="justify" style="width:730px; line-height:180%; font-size:14px; color:#000033; "> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbspHebeiHebei College of Industry and Technology (HBCIT) is Hebei Provincial Model Vocational Colleges and was entitled as "Top-Level College". In the meanwhile, HBCIT is a leading college in Hebei Province Metallurgical Vocation Education Group. In 2008, HBCIT was selected as "100 National Model Vocational Colleges" out of more than 1200 Vocational Colleges in China.   <br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  HBCIT is only one provincial metallurgical higher vocational college in Hebei Province, which was founded in 1958 and Xuanhua Longyan Steel Company Technology School is its initial name. Approved by the Ministry of Education of China in 1999, HBCIT founded by incorporating Hebei Metallurgy College for Staff and Workers and Hebei Metallurgical Industry College, and Xuanhua Steel Company College is its branch.
 <br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; HBCIT is located in Shijiazhuang city, the capital city in Hebei Province, The college area is almost 160 Acres , fixed assets is up to 0.3 Billion. The amount volume of Library Book is 0.897 Million. There are seven departments and some other divisions , which are as follows: Metal Material Engineering, Mechanical and Electronic Engineering, Environmental and Chemical Engineering, Information Engineering and Automation, Computer Technology, Architectural Engineering, Law and Economic trade, Department for Fundamental Courses, Department for Political Education and Physical Education, Department for Adult Education and Research Institute for Higher Vocational Education, The Research and Development Center for Applied Technology and Exchange Center for International Education. HBCIT has an enrollment of more than 10,000 students, and has over 600 staff and teachers. Nearly any big metallurgical company in China has our graduates, and the college has enjoyed the great reputation "Workshop Section Chiefs' Cradle" in Hebei Provincial Metallurgical Companies. 
<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The program focus is mainly based on engineering courses together with 45 applied technological majors and includes Art, Accounting, Economics and Trade and Business Management. Among them, Five majors are regarded as the State Pilot Major in Chinese teaching reform, 9 majors are Hebei Provincial Pilot Majors. Besides, there are 4 national level classical courses and 15 provincial level classical courses. 
 <br>
 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp 
 The facilities in HBCIT are advanced with 17 training bases in campus, including 5 sponsored by Central Government and 3 sponsored by Hebei Province Government and 130 training classroom also. In addition, there is one National Center for Vocational Skill Evaluation set in campus. HBCIT has been adhering to the principle of opening to the outside world. More than 100 teachers have been sent to Germany, America, Canada, Australia , Singapore and Taiwan for further learning and experience. More than 20 foreign language teachers have been introduced to teach oral and practical English to our students since 2000. HBCIT was approved to be one of the international exchange schools under the Sino-Canada joint venture educational exchange program. In 2001, a joint venture program-Hotel Management was set up with TST International Company in Singapore. In 2002, another two joint venture majors set up; they were Accounting and Computer Networking and Technical Support between our college and Seneca College of Applied Arts and Technology in Canada. Now several students are studying, practicing, working in Canada and Singapore. In May of 2005, A Top-Up program was made between our college and Middlesex Universities in London. In 2006, a good cooperative relationship was built between HBCIT and Nova Scotia Community College (NSCC) and a series of educational exchange activities have been held. In May of 2010, one delegation, including more than 10 teachers from NSCC came to our college for the purpose to carry out their Field School Program and strengthen mutual understanding and further cooperation between us. This was their fourth time to send delegation to our college. 
 <br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;   HBCIT has made close cooperation relations with metallurgical industries and large number of enterprises by persisting in the guideline of "Basing on metallurgy, Serving Hebei Province, Facing the whole nation". HBCIT places great emphasis on improving employment rate for graduates. A guidance office for recruitment and employment was set up earlier in Hebei Province and HBCIT has established good business relationships with many famous companies in China and a large number of graduates have gained job position in these companies. 
 <br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;    Now HBCIT is trying its best to make more contributions to the local economic construction, especially to make great efforts to boost Hebei Provincial Steel Industry's soaring development. 
